Compute a manifold for gene expression count data

compute_manifold.Rd

Compute a manifold for gene expression count data

Usage

compute_manifold(
  counts,
  method = "neighbor",
  preprocess = TRUE,
  ncores = 1,
  nfeatures = 3000,
  dims = 20,
  neighbors = 20
)

Arguments

counts

An expression count matrix. The rows correspond to genes and the columns correspond to cells. It can be sparse.

method

Method for estimating the manifold. Can be either "SAVER", which uses SAVER to recover the true expression, or 'neighbor', which uses nearest neighbors to approximate the true expression

preprocess

Whether the expression count matrix should be preprocessed, where all genes with zero counts will removed. Default is TRUE.

ncores

Number of cores to use. Default is 1. (SAVER only)

nfeatures

Number of features to use for FindVariableFeatures. Default is 3000. (Neighbor-based only)

dims

Number of dimensions for nearest neighbors. Default is 20.(Neighbor-based only)

neighbors

Number of neighbors to output. Default is 20. (Neighbor-based only)

Value

A matrix of estimated gene expressions.

tms_marrow_counts <- tms_marrow$Marrow@assays@data$counts
rownames(tms_marrow_counts) <- rownames(tms_marrow$Marrow)
colnames(tms_marrow_counts) <- colnames(tms_marrow$Marrow)
tms_marrow_counts <- as(tms_marrow_counts, "dgCMatrix")

# Subset age groups and cell types
subset_ages <- which(tms_marrow$Marrow$age %in% c("3m", "30m"))
subset_cell_types <- which(tms_marrow$Marrow$cell_ontology_class %in% c(
  "hematopoietic precursor cell", "megakaryocyte-erythroid progenitor cell",
  "precursor B cell"
))
tms_marrow_counts <- tms_marrow_counts[, intersect(subset_ages, subset_cell_types)]

# Compute the manifold using both methods
tms_marrow_manifold_saver <- compute_manifold(tms_marrow_counts, method = "SAVER")
